annotation.TEXT: Yep, this one's number 3.
Aw, now Sanae's small and weak, thanks to that Remilia and my sloppy playing.
Sorry, but I think the Mechakoopas are out sick with the flu today. You know how this season can get with that. I just hope they're taking it easy and eating plenty of chicken soup.
Okay, you can't slide-kill Nazrin. Good to know.
Looks like a mouse infestation has taken over this place. Better be careful.
Whoa, geez!
KA-BOOOOM!!!
Alright, looks like we've got some layer 2 shenanigans going on here.
Whoa, what the heck happened to that Sumo Brother? It's like mutated, bad. I guess they started to change the graphics for that guy, but stopped halfway through, or something.
Yay, we get to celebrate with party ribbons that hover in midair over this house that we never saw before in this game at all!
One left... Now, at this point, I think utilizing the Flandre platforms for a moment may be a good idea.
...with Yoshi! Hi, Yoshi!
Dang, Thwimpy Kisume... Why are you in a lousy sprite slot?
You're welcome!
Dang it, Alice! Get out of the way! I'm trying to kill that Thwimp!
Whoa, I'd better hurry up!
Ooh, 7650 is Namco's favorite number, I think...
...And Alices that fall to their doom when their bubbles burst.
Good thing I knew that I'd be safe down there. Now, I've gotta be more careful around these boingers...
And, that's it for this level. I think 300 seconds was a very appropriate time limit here.
Whoa, what's with that Porcu-Puffer? Also, if you saw a video glitch there, I blame YouTube, as my original movie file is perfectly fine.
Ah, but there's another cyan star, so Sanae can become big and strong again!
Whoa, hello! Fortunately, that maverick Yukkuri was in the proper sprite slot for my shell to clobber it!
Good thing there was a cyan star nearby when that happened.
According to brashup2, this message here says, "When you find all of the goals, the clear rate will change from a number to kanji."
Ooh, a multi-coin block that gives out coins worth piece-of-Remilia-hat-10 points each!
Oh, hey, I just thought of something I could try here...

Hello, and welcome to the finale of Hakurei Adventure Mission! Yes, I've decided that I'm going to cram every remaining level into this episode, regardless of how long they are! Now, let's begin with this palm tree level, Extra Mission: Insanity LV1!
Also, now Sanae's big and strong, thanks to that cyan star.
LOL, glitch!
No clue. It's just... there, I guess.
Man, the switching platforms makes this tricky, but I can do this!
Whoa, Banzai Bill! What happened to your face, dude? Also, LOL at the pumpkin head Rex!
Oh, man. Why are those Remilias all wearing black for this? And why does the third one have three eyes?
Gah, I'm not paying attention! Not that it matters much this time, since I can quickly regrow right here.
That must be a new breed of fish they're working on. Also, apparently pink is "in", when it comes to maces now.
Also, fortunately, that shell was in the right sprite slot to KO it. Can I get it to work on some of the Yukkuris as well?
Ooh, looks like somewhat tricky platforming...
Oh, we're done? Oh, but is there solid ground over here? Just gotta make sure, because I do not want to get Kaizo trapped!
Hi, Yoshi! ...Wait, you're not the real Yoshi! What the heck?
Oh, wow. There's actually a Touhou song in this hack? What a concept!
Ooh, what's down here?
Well, at least the time I wasted back there didn't hurt me, since I still got to the goal with plenty of time to spare.
Alright, Reimu, you're up! Hit a homer and win the game for us!

And there was a perfect example of that "ascending" glitch that I hate. When I spin jumped on the Thwimp and Goomba at the same time, I bounced off the Thwimp, and then the game saw that I was ascending when checking for my collision with the Goomba, and decided that it had hit me.
BGM: Earthbound - Pokey Means Business
Well, these bombs aren't much of a threat. Even if I didn't have the shell, I could always just wait for them to time out!
BGM: Touhou 9 - PoFV - Marisa's Theme - Oriental Dark Flight
A green ribbon?
Whoa, hey there, death. How's it going? Now, I don't think I'm ready to kick the bucket yet, so I'm just going to carefully bounce past you...
Oh, there's my growth star. Awesome.
Ah, so this level has a midpoint too. Also, I think this level began with only 300 seconds, unlike the 400 seconds I started with in the previous two palm tree levels.
BGM: Kirby 64 - Zero-Two Battle
However, I believe this is going to take a while (especially since the shell is missing some of the bullets), so I'm going to take part of this footage up to ludicrous speed!
Dang it, Marisa! Why'd you have to be flying so low there? Well, at least I can regrow myself here, but I'm not going to backtrack for firepower at this point.
LOL, looks like we've got a bit of a Flandre glitch here! (I didn't think I was KO-ing them that fast...)
Oh, yeah. I think someone complained that I didn't stay in the previous level that had this music for longer. Well, here you go. You should be able to listen to more of this music here!
Well, maybe if I could aim properly...
Ah, so there's a midpoint in this level... I don't think the previous palm tree level had a midpoint. Maybe this means this level will be longer.
Okay, this level also starts with 300 seconds, and it looks like it involves logs and Kisumes.
Gah! Stupid mask koopa shell Thwimp! Fortunately, I can backtrack for that cyan star I just passed.
Aww, and you know what? I probably completely wasted my time there, since I'm close to getting a 1-up through coins anyway. Oh, well.
Ooh, a green star! Now Sanae's got yellow hair and is packing firepower!
Alright, Sanae, it's time for you to take on the final palm tree level, Extra Mission: Insanity LV4!
Wait for it...
Darn it, why did that Thwomp Yukkuri have to be in the worst sprite slot?
Ah, so green ribbons give you life. Interesting...
And that's game! ...Wait! Oh, no! Don't Kaizo trap me!!!
Okay, Kisume, you can stop hugging me now.
Dang, I gotta pay more attention for those mavericks. I'm glad I'm not necessarily a one-hit-point-wonder in this level!
Whoa, holy crap! Of course there would be a quick-time event here! Fortunately my reflexes were sharp! Now, let's take down these Flandres!
Yeah, if I kick this shell into here, and park my butt on top of the right cannon, I can farm for lives here!
Ha, you bullets are no match for me as long as my butt is down!
Yeah, nailed it!
Argh! Well, at least those power up stars are reusable, though I think that may be promoting sloppy playing...
Ah, yellow stars are coins, and the cyan star embiggens my noble spirit. Excellent.
...And bullets and bubbles.
D'oh. I never did think to recheck the title screen after finishing this, so maybe I'll show off the kanji that's now there in a future bonus episode at some point.
Yeah, more firepower! (How come Reimu didn't get any fire power ups in her palm tree levels?) Also, watch out for death, who I guess likes to hang out here, too.
Ah, now a red square has surrounded the palm tree, indicating the level is cleared. Up next will be Extra Mission: Insanity LV2, as soon as I can get Sanae over to it...
Ack! I thought I could deliver the necessary five shots in time. That's okay. I can just go back and repower up!
Oh, also, I'm going to keep swapping a life back and forth so that the currently active player is always the one that's missing a life, so that if I do earn a 1-up somewhere, it'll be meaningful.
Wait, shouldn't "Reimu" be red and "Sanae" be green?
Well, except for the Spike Tops, everybody here is unchanged.
Alright, Reimu, it's your turn. Let's go and take on Extra Mission: Insanity LV3, which I think is in the upper-left corner, maybe?
And here's some duders who you can't pronounce the names of unless you know what those Japanese symbols mean.
Heck, yeah. Going through a pipe for no reason other than "it's there".
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Metal Version (reused again)

Oh, whew! I thought Reimu was going to suffer her first death at the last possible second there! Thankfully, for some weird reason, the death blocks didn't kill me when I passed through them during the victory music there. Is it because I was riding the Flandre platform?
And let's watch the credits roll...
Oh, actually, I hope another bomb shows up. I want to try something.
So, what's the deal with this floating water here?
Okay, now that I know it's safe, I'm outta here!
Hey, has someone been experimenting with an invisible potion around here? Well, let them know it's not working entirely perfectly! I can still see a few body parts... sort of.
BGM: Star Fox SNES - Corneria (reused)
Wow, that Alice tried to kill me! If I didn't abort my jump, I probably would've been knocked into the waiting arms of death there!
Whoa! Those bouncy blocks are here too?!
And there's a midpoint here too. I wonder why the first palm tree level didn't have a midpoint... Or did I just miss it somehow?
And with that, all four palm tree levels are completed! Now, for the final mission...
Oh, man. Do I have to bullet jump here? ...No, I guess not, but I'm going to anyway!
Okay, that's enough of that. I only needed one life to max out anyway.
Ah, there we go! I just wanted to get that effect once. Okay, enough wasting time. Let's move on.
Okay, I found my bomb, so let's see if I can get this trick to work. I think the successfulness of this move depends on sprite slots as well...
Whoa, serious color problems here. Also, I was kind of hoping to see the giant Mario head for the Big Boo here, instead of a messed up version of the masked glasses guy.
Apparently, Flandre is one of the least screwed-up enemy showings here.

And that's "the end" I guess. Hey there, Reimu! How's it going? Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Hakurei Adventure Mission! Now, I do have ideas for one or two bonus episodes, but they may take a while to put together, assuming I go through with them. Well, anyway, good bye for now!
Ah, a bomb! That should work, regardless of which sprite slot everything is in!
It's final boss time!
A screen transition, in this hack? Blasphemy!
Whoa, that was close! Be careful, because I guess the foul stench of death is still around!
Ah, yes. This level begins with 400 seconds, and is clearly more than one screen in length. Yep, we've got a full-length level here!
Oh, we're done already? Well, that wasn't too terribly long. (So, I guess 400 seconds was way more than enough, and the level probably could've gotten away with a 300-second time limit.)
Whoa, there was a ceiling up there that I wasn't expecting. Fortunately, it didn't result in me getting hurt.
And here's some of those duders that I encountered during the game, and some others, like that Wiggler train, that I never met before!
Whoa, those colors are really screwed up, especially Marisa's and Nitori's! Also, I always wonder why Nintendo spelled "pirhana" like that... It should be "piranha", right?
